Foot and Mouth Disease - Uganda 19980309184044
Date: 13 Apr 2000
From: Marjorie P. Pollack <pollackmp@mindspring.com>
Source: Africa News Service 12 Apr 2000 [edited

According to a report by the Africa News Service, the barara district
office has instructed all livestock markets in the district to close down
immediately following an outbreak of food and mouth disease (FMD). The
quarantine will also affect Kamwema market in Endizi in Tanzania and the
area along Tanzanian-Uganda Boarder have been ordered to close immediately
for effective control of FMD. Mbarara District Veterinary Officer, Dr.
William Gasasira issued this order at a meeting with veterinarians from
Bukoba in Tanzania and Mbarara at his offices in Mbarara.
--
Marjorie P. Pollack, M.D.
<pollackmp@mindspring.com>
